1
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:45,800
WEIYANG PUBLIC
SECURITY BUREAU NANSHAN BRANCH

2
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:46,840
Over the past few days, we've checked in

3
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:48,480
with taxi drivers and tricycle operators
across several districts.

4
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:50,080
None of them picked up
any students heading to Yuanlongli.

5
00:01:50,160 --> 00:01:51,040
What about your side?

6
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,320
Did you check

7
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:53,440
the supermarkets and shops
around the school?

8
00:01:55,080 --> 00:01:56,560
We have a lead.

9
00:01:56,640 --> 00:01:57,480
Han Zi'ang finally spoke.

10
00:01:58,320 --> 00:01:59,480
What did he say?

11
00:02:00,160 --> 00:02:01,240
Something like this.

12
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:08,440
"Charon.

13
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:10,400
Charon the ferryman

14
00:02:11,160 --> 00:02:12,600
carries souls to Yinyi Village.

15
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:13,960
Horse.

16
00:02:15,320 --> 00:02:16,640
The Trojan Horse.

17
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,160
It eats people.

18
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:21,440
It's going to eat you."

19
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:22,960
What are you on about?

20
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:25,800
He's not fully recovered yet.

21
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:27,360
He's rambling about anime stuff.

22
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:29,840
- Nonsense?
- Not exactly.

23
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:31,640
Explain that.

24
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:34,800
I can't quite piece it together yet,

25
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:36,520
but I think what he said

26
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:39,240
might be connected
to the real-world crime scene.

27
00:02:39,320 --> 00:02:40,320
We should try to decipher it.

28
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:45,360
What kind of outfit
is that for a detective?

29
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:46,600
- I was trying to…
- Enough.

30
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:48,240
Stick to your job.

31
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:49,840
Head back to the hospital
and stay with Han Zi'ang.

32
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:52,400
When he's fully awake, question him again.

33
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:55,160
Stop jumping to conclusions.
You're throwing us off.

34
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:56,320
Go on.

35
00:02:57,040 --> 00:02:58,840
We've checked all the shops
around the school

36
00:02:58,920 --> 00:03:00,360
and pulled every camera we could find.

37
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:02,360
Still, nothing unusual turned up.

38
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:13,440
WHAT DOES TROJAN HORSE MEAN?

39
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:16,040
If Qu Dahai could make sense of that,

40
00:03:16,120 --> 00:03:18,120
he wouldn't be on this Earth anymore.

41
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:21,200
It's not entirely his fault.

42
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:24,080
What Han Zi'ang said
isn't easy to figure out.

43
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:33,280
If this Yinyi Village

44
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:35,760
refers to Yuanlongli,

45
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:38,800
then could Charon the ferryman

46
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:41,480
be some kind of transport?

47
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:44,760
The task force is focusing on vehicles.

48
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:47,160
Commercial cars and tricycles.

49
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,440
What about ride shares?

50
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:50,800
What ride shares?

51
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:54,400
Some shops restock
in the morning and at night.

52
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:57,200
Drivers pick up extra passengers
along the way.

53
00:03:57,920 --> 00:03:59,960
Unlicensed cars like that are too random

54
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:01,440
to track down.

55
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:06,160
These five kids skipped school,

56
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:08,880
but none of the road cameras caught them.

57
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:11,120
I think we should check

58
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:14,960
for construction sites near their school.

59
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:16,120
If there is,

60
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:18,079
it could mess with the cameras.

61
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:20,480
Where's the map? Let me see it.

62
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:38,440
DANFENG MIDDLE SCHOOL,

63
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:40,440
WEIYANG NO. 2 MIDDLE SCHOOL
WEIYANG NO. 4 MIDDLE SCHOOL

64
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:49,400
Focus here.

65
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:50,840
BINCHUAN DISTRICT

66
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:54,480
WEIYANG STADIUM, WENZHUANG

67
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:22,880
JIAJIA GROCERY

68
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:38,280
Where're my cigarettes?

69
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:50,200
I dropped a pack on the road.

70
00:05:50,280 --> 00:05:51,600
I'll make it up to you.

71
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:53,600
It's fine.

72
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:55,200
Let me introduce myself.

73
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:57,480
I'm Yuan Ziqiang. What about you?

74
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:00,120
Here's the thing.

75
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:03,240
I'm driving
to the provincial capital today

76
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:05,120
to meet up with some friends
from my hometown.

77
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:07,480
You've been saying
you want to go to Beijing.

78
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:09,480
There's a train
from the provincial capital.

79
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:11,880
Do you want to hitch a ride?

80
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:13,360
I can drop you off there.

81
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:25,600
About this tall.

82
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:28,120
She's wearing a green jacket
and dark jeans.

83
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:29,200
About this tall.

84
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:30,400
Have you seen this girl?

85
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:32,160
About this tall.
She's wearing a green jacket.

86
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:33,120
No.

87
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:34,480
- Mister, have you seen this girl?
- Mister,

88
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:36,360
have you seen this girl?

89
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:38,560
No.

90
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:40,120
Alright. Thanks.

91
00:06:41,640 --> 00:06:43,840
- How much?
- Two yuan for half a kilo.

92
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:45,560
Wrap up these three.

93
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:47,480
JIAJIA GROCERY

94
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:55,440
It's hot.

95
00:07:02,280 --> 00:07:03,320
Guys,

96
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,480
we've checked eight stops.

97
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:06,640
But there's not a single trace.

98
00:07:06,720 --> 00:07:08,720
That little tyke is probably gone.

99
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:10,560
At this rate,

100
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:11,920
we'll still be at it by Chinese New Year.

101
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:15,320
Let's head back

102
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:17,280
and come up with a new plan.

103
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:20,040
Captain Ran told us to work the route.
There has to be a reason.

104
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:21,120
Finish up and keep going.

105
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:23,840
He's here.

106
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:28,680
How's it going here?

107
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:32,000
We've got this covered.
Why don't you get some rest?

108
00:07:32,080 --> 00:07:33,120
- You've been running yourself ragged.
- Here.

109
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:34,840
Grab a bite.

110
00:07:35,840 --> 00:07:37,760
He Xiaohe is just
as insensible as her dad.

111
00:07:37,840 --> 00:07:39,640
Look at what she's doing to Captain Ran.

112
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:41,760
Don't say that.

113
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:43,440
I share the blame
for what happened to her.

114
00:07:43,520 --> 00:07:45,920
If I hadn't pushed Sir
to take on that case,

115
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:48,240
his family might not have fallen apart.

116
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,960
You keep calling him "Sir".

117
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:52,320
Does He Yuanhang even deserve that?

118
00:07:56,280 --> 00:07:57,960
JIAJIA GROCERY

119
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:03,840
JIAJIA GROCERY

120
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,280
Did we check the supermarket?

121
00:08:13,840 --> 00:08:15,840
We just got to this street
and are about to check it out.

122
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:20,920
<i>"Suddenly, over the stream</i>
<i>We heard a pipa sound</i>

123
00:08:21,560 --> 00:08:24,400
<i>I forgot to go home,</i>
<i>And the guest stood spell-bound"</i>

124
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:27,200
Pen. Pen.

125
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:32,440
<i>"Song of a Pipa Player,</i> by Bai Juyi.

126
00:08:33,039 --> 00:08:34,080
In the tenth year of Yuanhe's reign…"

127
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:35,559
What can I get you, misters?

128
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:37,400
We're with the Nanshan Branch.

129
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:39,520
Have you seen this girl?

130
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,120
MISSING PERSONS

131
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:46,120
Have you seen her?

132
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:55,040
Go back to your studies.

133
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:03,440
<i>"Suddenly, over the stream</i>
<i>We heard a pipa sound</i>

134
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:06,680
<i>I forgot to go home,</i>
<i>and the guest stood spell-bound.</i>

135
00:09:06,760 --> 00:09:09,360
<i>We followed the music to its source,</i>

136
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:13,040
<i>but heard the pipa stop,</i>
<i>and no music in the air.</i>

137
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:16,520
<i>We moved our boat towards</i>
<i>the one whence came the strain,</i>

138
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:20,640
<i>brought back the lamp,</i>
<i>asked for more wine and drank again.</i>

139
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:24,080
<i>Repeatedly, we called</i>
<i>For the fair player still"</i>

140
00:09:26,160 --> 00:09:27,120
Your son is working hard.

141
00:09:28,680 --> 00:09:30,480
He's in high school,
but his grades aren't great.

142
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:31,760
So I keep an eye on his studies.

143
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:33,000
Recite it again.

144
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:34,960
<i>"Song of a Pipa Player,</i> by Bai Juyi.

145
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:36,880
In the tenth year of Yuanhe's reign…"

146
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:39,600
Let's move on to the next shop.

147
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:41,640
Take care.

148
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:54,120
Putting on a show is way harder

149
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:56,000
than gaming.

150
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:57,560
When that girl gets back with supplies,

151
00:09:57,640 --> 00:09:58,800
I'm going to send her home.

152
00:09:58,880 --> 00:10:01,040
- I'm heading inside to practice.
- Hold on.

153
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:03,600
Wait till the cops are out of sight.

154
00:10:06,280 --> 00:10:08,240
We haven't checked
a hardware store up ahead,

155
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:10,160
a barbershop, and a mahjong parlor.

156
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:13,160
Wait. Stay here.

157
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:14,280
Wait?

158
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:15,280
How long?

159
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:20,840
Five minutes. We'll go back to that shop.

160
00:10:27,640 --> 00:10:29,080
Hurry up. Cover for me.

161
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:30,160
Come on.

162
00:10:42,760 --> 00:10:44,000
Is he your son too?

163
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,400
You do magic tricks,

164
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:53,040
and your son changes faces.

165
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,320
Five minutes, and he has lost weight?

166
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:01,760
Officer, I want to come clean.

167
00:11:02,560 --> 00:11:04,040
I saw that girl.

168
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:09,160
<i>Everyone, look to your left.</i>

169
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:12,440
<i>This is the first stop</i>
<i>of our Mount Wu tour.</i>

170
00:11:12,520 --> 00:11:13,720
<i>Seeing flowers in the fog.</i>

171
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:15,920
<i>If we come back in three or four months,</i>

172
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,200
<i>you'll see flowers in the fog</i>

173
00:11:18,280 --> 00:11:19,840
<i>and fog among the flowers.</i>

174
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:21,800
<i>The heavier the fog,</i>

175
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:23,280
<i>the more dangerous it is</i>
<i>to head up to the mountain.</i>

176
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:26,280
<i>Back on August 24th, 1995,</i>

177
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:28,360
<i>there was an accident.</i>

178
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:30,040
<i>So once you reach the resort,</i>

179
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:33,240
<i>remember this, do not</i>
<i>go up the mountain on your own.</i>

180
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:51,920
JINGLIAN TEMPLE TUNNEL

181
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,000
ROUTE 15 WEIYANG STADIUM TO WENZHUANG

182
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:13,680
You're not a trafficker, are you?

183
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:15,840
Sorry?

184
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:18,760
You're not a trafficker, are you?

185
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,080
Get off at the next stop.

186
00:12:25,960 --> 00:12:26,920
Find your own way back.

187
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:40,720
JIAJIA GROCERY

188
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:42,400
Mangkun, head over to Nanhu Market.

189
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:44,040
Talk to the vendors.

190
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:48,040
Find out who she hung out with.

191
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:49,800
What about the four of them?

192
00:12:52,280 --> 00:12:53,240
IDs.

193
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:54,520
We…

194
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:56,000
We don't have IDs.

195
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:59,080
They're in the cybercafé without IDs?

196
00:12:59,160 --> 00:13:01,440
Officer, this is an illegal cybercafé.

197
00:13:01,520 --> 00:13:03,760
It's not his fault. We're all over 18.

198
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:06,120
We sold our IDs for money

199
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,960
to pay for our training and competitions.

200
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:10,240
This is gaming, not a competition.

201
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:11,400
Qu.

202
00:13:12,280 --> 00:13:14,400
- Do you have surveillance here?
- Yes.

203
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:33,560
Officer, this is the footage
from the past week.

204
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:39,360
Officer,

205
00:13:39,440 --> 00:13:41,800
we really did see her passed out
in the alley late at night.

206
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:44,360
We were afraid she'd freeze,
so we brought her back.

207
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:46,480
This money-grabber squeezes
money out of us every day.

208
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:48,520
Even if you break wind here,

209
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:50,720
she'll chase you down and charge you
an air pollution fee.

210
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:51,760
Sometimes,

211
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:54,240
when Xiaohe saw us training hard,

212
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:56,200
she would chip in
and buy us instant noodles.

213
00:13:56,280 --> 00:13:58,480
Yeah. She's not stingy.

214
00:13:58,560 --> 00:14:00,840
She said she was saving up
to go to Beijing.

215
00:14:00,920 --> 00:14:01,680
Beijing?

216
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:04,040
- To learn rock music.
- That's right.

217
00:14:04,120 --> 00:14:05,240
Go to Beijing to learn rock music.

218
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:07,200
When did she say that?

219
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:10,280
ROUTE 15 WEIYANG STADIUM TO WENZHUANG
DONGLIWA STATION

220
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:29,120
We'll stay there for the night.

221
00:14:31,160 --> 00:14:33,240
Didn't you say we were leaving today?

222
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:35,760
My friend said
some of them haven't arrived yet.

223
00:14:35,840 --> 00:14:37,440
We'll head out together tomorrow
once everyone's here.

224
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:46,800
HAPPY SHOPPING MART

225
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:54,040
YOUCHENG HOTEL

226
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:15,760
Come on in.

227
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:24,320
Kid,

228
00:15:24,920 --> 00:15:26,320
you're suspicious of everything.

229
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:30,000
Take a look at this.

230
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:36,360
YUAN ZIQIANG'S IDENTITY CARD

231
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:40,560
I'm not lying, right?

232
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:41,480
CITIZEN IDENTIFICATION

233
00:15:42,360 --> 00:15:43,840
You can have it if you want.

234
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:57,000
Captain Ran, look at this.

235
00:15:59,680 --> 00:16:01,640
This is footage from 11:05 a.m.

236
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:03,120
After this man

237
00:16:03,640 --> 00:16:05,880
gave Xiaohe some money, she headed out

238
00:16:05,960 --> 00:16:07,080
and hasn't come back since.

239
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:13,080
That guy with the glasses

240
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:14,920
always had Xiaohe
pick up cigarettes for him.

241
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:17,120
He never asked for change.
He's really generous.

242
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:32,840
What do you do for a living?

243
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:34,800
Construction.

244
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:37,920
I go back and forth between Weiyang
and the provincial capital very often.

245
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,000
And you?

246
00:16:39,080 --> 00:16:41,320
I noticed you've been staying
at the cybercafé every night.

247
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:42,960
Doesn't your family check on you?

248
00:16:58,320 --> 00:17:00,320
Alright. Food's almost ready.

249
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:06,920
Instant noodles again?

250
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:09,560
I eat that three times a day
at the cybercafé.

251
00:17:10,079 --> 00:17:11,800
It makes me sick just looking at it now.

252
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,400
Mister,

253
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:16,240
can you buy me a proper meal?

254
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:25,920
Little kid,

255
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:28,119
you're such a hassle.

256
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:38,200
Don't wander off.

257
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:39,840
It's not safe out there.

258
00:17:40,360 --> 00:17:42,240
You might get snatched.

259
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,960
- Who has the wanted list?
- I do.

260
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:18,920
I picked up this habit at the station.

261
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,280
I always carry it with me
whenever I'm out.

262
